Istanbul Prices Fell 0.7 Percent in June, Chamber Says

-- B y   A l i   B e r a t   M e r i c
-- 
2011-07-01T09:15:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-01/istanbul-prices-fell-0-7-percent-in-june-chamber-says-correct-.html
(Corrects change in cost of living index in first
paragraph.)  Prices in Istanbul,  Turkey ’s biggest
city, fell 0.7 percent in June, the city’s chamber of commerce
said.  Annual inflation in Istanbul accelerated to 6.4 percent in
June from 5.9 percent in May, the chamber said today, announcing
its cost of living index. Turkey’s state statistics agency will
announce nationwide price data for June on July 4.  Wholesale prices in the city fell 0.3 percent in the month,
the chamber said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ali Berat Meric in Ankara at 
 americ@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Bryant at 
 sbryant5@bloomberg.net  